- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper deals with the problem of finding the best approximate joint triangularizer of a set of noisy matrices, which involves solving a nonconvex optimization problem. This falls under the scope of numerical analysis. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the application of approximate joint matrix triangularization to canonical tensor decomposition, which is a common problem in machine learning. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper does not explicitly deal with social or information networks, but the problem of joint matrix triangularization has applications in signal processing, which is a subfield of information theory. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the problem of estimating the joint eigenstructure of a set of matrices, which has applications in linear algebra and information theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the problem of finding the best approximate joint triangularizer of a set of matrices, which involves solving a nonconvex optimization problem. This falls under the scope of algorithms and data structures.
